Technical Representation
The code layer is a symbolic demo only. It does not connect to wallets, blockchains, paid
services, private keys, seed phrases, or physical devices. It organizes the model, preserves the
founder signature, defines axioms, and supports future documentation.
Future Test Protocol
Future physical or computational claims should be separated from the manifesto layer. A
serious protocol should include claim definition, baseline measurement, experimental setup,
repeatable procedure, data log, error range, independent replication, and public result
summary.
